The paper deals with the evaluation of secrecy outage probability in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the impact of signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) on the secrecy outage probability, which is a common consideration in wireless networking (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a simple expression for the secrecy outage probability, which could be relevant to communication systems optimization (cs.SI) and network modeling (cs.COM).
